name: Here's Looking At You
description:
A fractal triangle with a twist. What I love about algorithmic art is that I can revisit what I've done and combine it with other works to create something quite different with it. In this case, I took my earlier work where I explored how to create effective looking eyes for algorithmic animals. My initial version of the fractal triangle was simply a series of coloured dots getting smaller and smaller. When combined, it becomes a series of disembodied eyes staring out from the darkness. 

Created in 2012.
